From: Trung Lê <8@tle.id.au>
Subject: appmgr: install Application Manager action files as executable

CDE's File Manager (dtfile) treats a file under
$(CDE_DATA_TOP)/appconfig/appmanager/$(LANG)/<group>/<Name> as an
action -- i.e. double-click runs the matching ACTION from the .dt
database -- only when:

  1. The file name matches an ACTION definition in *.dt, and
  2. The file has the execute bit set.

The action file itself documents this in its own contents:

    # If this file is executable and the name of the file matches an
    # entry in the action database (*.dt files), the CDE File Manager
    # will treat this file as an action.

Today the upstream source template programs/types/action is shipped
with mode 0644 and the appmgr.am rule cp's it verbatim into each
Application Manager entry (Desktop_Apps/Dtcalc etc.). Two problems
appear on Fedora:

  1. The cp preserves the 0644 source mode, so even before any
     packaging step the built-tree entries lack the exec bit.

  2. Fedora's rpm pipeline runs brp-mangle-shebangs after %install,
     which scans every executable file: if the first line is not a
     `#!` shebang, the script strips the exec bit and warns. The
     action template starts with `# ...` (regular comment, no `!`),
     so even when something earlier chmods +x, brp-mangle-shebangs
     reverses it before the cpio payload is built. The visible
     symptom: clicking Dtcalc in the Application Manager opens the
     action file in dtpad as text instead of launching dtcalc.

Two-part fix:

  - Prepend `#!/bin/sh` to programs/types/action so brp-mangle-shebangs
    accepts the file as a shell script and keeps the exec bit. dtfile
    never execs the action file body (it only consults the file name
    against the action DB), so the shebang is cosmetic for CDE's own
    use; if a user does run the file directly it harmlessly prints
    the final `echo "..."` line.

  - In programs/localized/templates/appmgr.am, chmod +x after the
    $(CP) so the BUILT_SOURCES entries are executable in the build
    tree. install then carries the bit through to DESTDIR.

--- a/programs/types/action
+++ b/programs/types/action
@@ -1,3 +1,4 @@
+#!/bin/sh
 %|nls-1-#This file represents a ...#|
 %|nls-2-##|
 %|nls-3-##|
--- a/programs/localized/templates/appmgr.am
+++ b/programs/localized/templates/appmgr.am
@@ -87,5 +87,7 @@ appmgr_allfiles = $(desktop_apps_SCRIPTS) $(graphics_SCRIPTS)		\
 BUILT_SOURCES = $(appmgr_allfiles)
 CLEANFILES = $(BUILT_SOURCES)

+# dtfile only treats these as actions if they're executable -- see the
+# self-documenting comment inside the programs/types/action template.
 $(appmgr_allfiles): $(ACTION)
-	$(CP) $(ACTION) $@ || $(RM) $@
+	$(CP) $(ACTION) $@ && chmod +x $@ || { $(RM) $@; exit 1; }
